The paper focuses on analyzing index structures for immutable data, which is a topic related to data structures and databases. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the importance of tamper-evident controls, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different index structures, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
